	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><placeName>New Orleans</placeName> <date>May 28th 1847</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Mr Isaac. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">A temporary absence from<lb/> <placeName>N. Orleans</placeName>&#44; to <placeName>Vicksburg</placeName> and very active employment since my return<lb/> leaving me very little time of my own&#44; are the only excuses I have<lb/> to offer for allowing your kind favor of <date>19th</date> ultimo to be so long unanswered.</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I have as yet been unable to procure any<lb/> suitable person to whom I can entrust <del>the</del> with proper confidence your<lb/> interest here&#44; &#38; the time for my departure to <placeName>Kentucky</placeName> &#40;say<lb/> <date>10th</date> next month&#41; will leave me so little time to find a<lb/> proper person that I am a loss what to do in the matter.<lb/>  I shall be absent all summer&#44; and am sorry for your<lb/> sake that this is the case as nothing would give me<lb/> more pleasure than to further your welfare&#44; knowing as I<lb/> do how essential it is for the interest of our religion&#44;<lb/> I will look out for some one who will undertake it<lb/> &#38; collect the subscriptions&#44; I believe I have in my<lb/> possession the amt of <persName>Brown&#39;s</persName>subscription 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi>. Year 3&#36;<lb/> <persName>A Block</persName> up to <date>1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> April 47</date> &#61; 3&#36; &#38; one other subscriber<lb/> whose name I forget 3&#36; this is all the money in my hand<lb/>  Address me here with instructions &#38; in my absence my<lb/> Father will attend to them.</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName>Mr. Kursheedt</persName> does not recommend the advertise<lb/>&#45;ment of the sale of Books &#38; his views generally being good</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>I have refrained from doing so&#44; there is such an apathy<lb/> here as to foode for the soul&#44; that there is no sale or<lb/> demand for anything of the kinde&#44; Its all money&#33;  Money<lb/> Money&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have seen nothing of <persName>Rabbi Cohen</persName> of <placeName><sic>Helon</sic>&#44; Palestine</placeName><lb/> but will be glad to state your wishes to the gentlemen of<lb/> our Congregation here.  I stated to <persName>Mr Levy</persName> your instruct<lb/>&#45;ions &#38; suppose he has written you&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I am dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Yours Truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">D. C. Labatt</persName></p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><placeName>Pennsylvania</placeName></p>
		</body>
